	(text "- CANH/L_+/- are a differential pair (120 ohm differential, 60 ohm odd-mode), and as such\n   trace width, spacing etc will need to be calculated at route-time\n- The abundance of ferrites is puzzling, but is what's recommended in the datasheet. The\n   ferrites will all be 0603 package, but the exact bead will have to be determined by the\n   100MHz impedance, and ZRX curve.\n- The ISOW1044 Datasheet recommends the BLM15EX331SN1, which is 330@100MHz.\n- Since the CAN lines are exposed, TVS diodes with 12V RWM on both CANH and CANL. For\n   reasoning, check the changelog.\n- The 60 + 60R termination is new to me, but is also recommended in the datasheet. This may\n   be swapped for a 120R if need be.\n- CAN_IN and STB are both GPIO outputs of the microcontroller. Need to be set manually in\n   code (NOT taken care of by the bxCAN peripheral)."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 23.114 138.938 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "0d585b46-0601-412a-b0c3-6fc7c52bf2e7")
	)
